        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>-- Observing fields
We plan to map the 6' (E-W) x 8' (N-S) area of OMC1. In order to 
reduce the number of pointings, the area is divided into two 
rectangle fields (see Fig. 2). The two fields cover the most of the 
N2H+ emitting region of OMC-1 HFS.
The science case 1 is for the Field-S (6' x 5' 20"). We plan to mosaic 
this region with a Nyquist sampling. The total numbers of pointings 
are 138 for the 12m array and 45 for the 7m array.

- Receiver and correlator settings
We use the band 3 receiver. The N2H+ 1-0, N15NH+ 1--0, 
HNC 1--0, CCS 7_6--6_7, and HC5N 35--34  lines are put in the LSB. 
Typical line width of the dense gas in this region is ~0.6 km/s 
(Tatematsu et al. 2008). In order to measure the line width and 
rotation in the cores, we need the high spectral resolution of ~0.2 km/s. 
The high spectral resolution is also necessary for observing the core-
forming flows in the filament, which is expected to be ~0.2 km/s. 
Therefore, we adopt the 61 kHz resolution mode for the spectral 
windows of the molecular lines.
The two basebands (3 &amp; 4) in the USB are dedicated to measure the 
continuum emission.  Therefore, we adopt the 2 GHz BW mode for 
these basebands.

-- Sensitivity
The antenna temperature of the N2H+ 1--0 line observed with 
the 18" beam (~7500 AU) of the NRO 45m telescope was 0.5--1.5 K, 
which corresponds to 1--3 K in the T_MB unit (Tatematsu et al. 2008).
 If most of the N2H+ emission arises from the cores with ~2000 AU 
size, the expected T_MB in the 3" beam becomes 7--15 K. We plan 
to achieve the rms noise level of ~0.6K, which should be enough to 
measure the line parameters and velocity structures of the N2H+ 
emission.
Under the 7th Octile weather condition (WVP = 6.186 mm), the 
required sensitivity could be achieved with an integration time 
(per pointing) of 17.9 second. In order to complete the map 
with 138 pointings, the required 12m array observing time 
becomes 1.35 hour.
The continuum sensitivity achieved with this integration time 
(17.9 sec.) is 0.27 mJy/beam (per pointing). Since each position 
of the field (except the edge of the mapping area) will be covered 
by 3 pointings, the expected continuum sensitivity will be 
0.15 mJy/beam. Under the assumption of T_dust = 15 K, 
kappa_0 = 0.01 cm^2/g at 1.3mm, and beta = 1--2, the corresponding 
mass sensitivity (1 sigma) is estimated to be 0.009 -- 0.02 M_sun.

-- ACA
As shown in Figures 1 &amp; 2, both continuum and line emission 
from this region contains the spatially extended component of 
~60" scale. Therefore, short spacing information provided by 
the ACA is important.
The required ACA 7m array and TP times are 2.7 hours and 
5.4 hours, respectively.


</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
