    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to observe the "hub-filament system (HFS)" of OMC-1 with 
molecular lines with high critical densities, N2H+ 1--0, N15NH+ 1--0, HNC 1--0,  
and CCS 7_8--6_7, and 3 mm dust continuum emission at an angular 
resolution of 3" (~1300 AU). The wide field view of ALMA at 3 mm (66") 
allows us to cover the entire OMC-1 HFS region of 6' (E-W) x 8' (N-S) with 
reasonable umber (183) of pointings. 
Our goals are to 1) identify the dense cores in this region down to substellar 
mass, and examine the core mass function and fragmentation process, 2) to 
study the kinematics of the cores such as line width, rotation and infall, 
and 3) to study the core-forming flows along the filaments at several 
thousand AU scale.
A comparison between the carbon-chain molecule, CCS, and the N-bearing 
molecule, N2H+, would be also helpful in studying the evolutionary stage 
of the cores.</prp:abstract>
